['377.                                  \xa0                     MARY                      BURGESS                                                                                                          was indicted for                                                          returning from transportation, and being found at large before the expiration of the time for which she was transported, against the statute            .', '(The record of the conviction produced and read by                \xa0                  Thomas                   Shelton                                                                                       , Esq. clerk of arraigns.)', ' \xa0                  JOHN                   OWEN                                                                                        sworn.', "I know the prisoner, I was present when she was tried in October, 1787, for stealing goods of Mr. Jackson, and was capitally convicted; in June, 1789, she received the King's pardon, on condition of being transported for seven years; I delivered her on board the Lady Juliana; she escaped soon after from the ship in Long Reach.", ' \xa0                  ROBERT                   DAWSON                                                                                        sworn.', 'I apprehended the prisoner in Billings-court, Petticoat-lane, on the 9th of August                   last; I found her in bed, in consequence of an information; she appearedSee original\xa0unwell;                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bear                                                                                        was in company with me,                \xa0                  Joseph                   Bear                                                                                        said that the woman sold old clothes, and behaved exceedingly well.', '                                                      GUILTY            ,                                                          Death            .', 'Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.']